35#include <assert.h>
36#include <libelf.h>
37#include <stdlib.h>

39#include "_libelf.h"

41#if ELFTC_HAVE_MMAP
42#include <sys/mman.h>
43#endif

45__RCSID("$NetBSD: elf_end.c,v 1.3 2016/02/20 02:43:42 christos Exp $");
46ELFTC_VCSID("Id: elf_end.c 3174 2015-03-27 17:13:41Z emaste ");
47
48int
49elf_end(Elf *e)
50{
51 Elf *sv;
52 Elf_Scn *scn, *tscn;
53
54 if (e == NULL || e->e_activations == 0)
55 return (0);
56
57 if (--e->e_activations > 0)
58 return (e->e_activations);
59
60 assert(e->e_activations == 0);
61
62 while (e && e->e_activations == 0) {
63 switch (e->e_kind) {
64 case ELF_K_AR:
65 /*
66 * If we still have open child descriptors, we
67 * need to defer reclaiming resources till all
68 * the child descriptors for the archive are
69 * closed.
70 */
71 if (e->e_u.e_ar.e_nchildren > 0)
72 return (0);
73 break;
74 case ELF_K_ELF:
75 /*
76 * Reclaim all section descriptors.
77 */
78 STAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(scn, &e->e_u.e_elf.e_scn, s_next,
79 tscn)
80 scn = _libelf_release_scn(scn);
81 break;
82 case ELF_K_NUM:
83 assert(0);
84 default:
85 break;
86 }
87
88 if (e->e_rawfile) {
89 if (e->e_flags & LIBELF_F_RAWFILE_MALLOC)
90 free(e->e_rawfile);
91#if ELFTC_HAVE_MMAP
92 else if (e->e_flags & LIBELF_F_RAWFILE_MMAP)
93 (void) munmap(e->e_rawfile, e->e_rawsize);
94#endif
95 }
96
97 sv = e;
98 if ((e = e->e_parent) != NULL)
99 e->e_u.e_ar.e_nchildren--;
100 sv = _libelf_release_elf(sv);
101 }
102
103 return (0);
104}
